# CopyPageButton

A button that copies the current page content as text to the clipboard. Two variants:

- **`default`** ‚Äî full button with clipboard icon + "Copy page" label. Rendered in the page body (e.g. under the H1) on every API page.
- **`icon`** ‚Äî clipboard-only button with a `title="Copy page"` tooltip. Rendered in the sticky API toolbar. Hidden by default; reveals itself once the main (default-variant) button scrolls behind the sticky toolbar, so the page-copy action is always within reach. Visibility is driven by sampling `getBoundingClientRect` on scroll/resize rather than an IntersectionObserver against the viewport, because the latter would only fire after the target left the *entire* viewport ‚Äî well past the moment it disappeared behind the sticky region.

## Properties

| Name | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `labels` | `{ "Copy page": string; "Copied": string }` | required | i18n strings. Localized in the `CopyPageButtonIsland.astro` wrapper. |
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'icon'` | `'default'` | Layout. `'icon'` drops the label and adds the scroll-driven visibility behavior. |
| `watchTargetSelector` | `string` | `.copy-page-button:not(.copy-page-button--icon)` | Icon variant only. CSS selector for the element this button shadows; the icon appears once it scrolls behind the sticky anchor. |
| `stickyAnchorSelector` | `string` | `.api-toolbar` | Icon variant only. CSS selector for the sticky container whose bottom edge marks where the watch target is considered hidden. Resolved via `closest()` from the icon button. |

## Behavior

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| Mouseenter | Begins fetching the `.md` version of the page from `docs.datadoghq.com` |
| Click | Copies the fetched text (or DOM-extracted fallback) to clipboard |
| After copy | Shows "Copied!" with a checkmark icon for 3 seconds |
| Cache | Results are cached per URL to avoid redundant fetches |

## Fallback

If the `.md` fetch fails (e.g. during local development), the component extracts text from the DOM by walking the `.prose` content area. It converts headings to markdown `#` format, links to `[text](url)` format, and preserves block structure.

## Visual states

The button has two visual states:

- **Default**: clipboard icon + "Copy page"
- **Copied**: clipboard-with-checkmark icon + "Copied" (resets after 3 seconds)

Both label strings render at all times ‚Äî the inactive one is hidden with `visibility: hidden` so the button keeps a constant width. The icon stays in place when the label flips between states.

## Usage

API pages render the localized `CopyPageButtonIsland.astro` wrapper, which forwards translated `labels` to the underlying Preact component. The wrapper is used twice: once in the page body (default variant) and once in `ApiLayout`'s sticky toolbar (icon variant).

```astro
<!-- in the page body, below the <h1> -->
<CopyPageButtonIsland lang={lang} />

<!-- in ApiLayout's toolbar (already wired up) -->
<CopyPageButtonIsland lang={currentLang} variant="icon" />
```

The icon-variant island finds the main button via a CSS selector at hydration time. If no main button is present on the page, the icon variant stays hidden.

It appears on all API pages: the index, category pages, individual operation pages, and static pages (rate limits, scopes, using the API).
